verses.roman:
baḍa śākhā, upaśākhā, tāra upaśākhā
yata upajila tāra ke karibe lekhā

synonyms: baḍa śākhā—the big branches; upaśākhā—subbranches; tāra—their; upaśākhā—subbranches; yata—all that; upajila—grew; tāra—of them; ke—who; karibe—can count; lekhā—or write.
translation: These branches and subbranches and their subbranches became so numerous that no one can actually write about them.
